<subSubSection id="EA9EDA8EFF97FFB00CBAFF73FE80FF73" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF97FFB00CBAFF73FE80FF73" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB00CBAFF73FEF9FF17" bold="true" box="[199,334,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a reference to the locality where the 
<typeStatus id="7D3F37A7FF97FFB00FF8FF73FC02FF17" box="[901,949,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">type</typeStatus>
series was collected, near the Pacific coast of 
<collectingCountry id="DA93C995FF97FFB00CCBFF5FFE84FF73" box="[182,307,187,213]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EA9EDA8EFF97FFB00CBAFF3AFC0CFD9B" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF97FFB00CBAFF3AFC0CFD9B" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB00CBAFF3AFEF8FF5E" bold="true" box="[199,335,222,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Comments.</emphasis>
Specimens examined from Santa Rosa National Park consistently exhibit a denser punctation, lighter coloration of antennae and legs, conspicuously dense setation, and a sulcus coming from the mesepisternal pit to the posterior edge of the mesepisternum when compared to 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF97FFB00FF9FEC3FB9BFEE7" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[900,1068,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiventris">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB00FF9FEC3FB9BFEE7" box="[900,1068,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">C. longiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We examined a series of specimens of the latter coming from various localities across the Neotropical region and concluded that, even though 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF97FFB009FEFEAFFEAAFE2F" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiventris">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB009FEFEAFFEAAFE2F" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">C. longiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may exhibit variations in size and coloration, the characters used to differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF97FFB00962FE8BFA2BFE2F" authority="Lepeco &amp; Melo, 2022" authorityName="Lepeco &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1311,1436,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pacifica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB00962FE8BFA2BFE2F" box="[1311,1436,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">C. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB00CEAFE77FF43FE0B" bold="true" box="[151,244,403,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="8BC3E86CFF97FFB00CEAFE77FF43FE0B" box="[151,244,403,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
do not overlap. Differences in setation among species of 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF97FFB00FE6FE77FBF7FE0B" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[923,1088,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB00FE6FE77FBF7FE0B" box="[923,1088,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">Clystopsenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were already noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF97FFB00925FE77FF53FE77" author="Gauld, I. D." pageId="7" pageNumber="132" pagination="468 - 470" refId="ref6569" refString="Gauld, I. D. (1995) Scolebythidae. In: Hanson, P. E. &amp; Gauld, I. D. (Eds.), Hymenoptera of Costa Rica. Oxford University Press, Oxford, pp. 468 - 470." type="book chapter" year="1995">Gauld (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, which mentions that a female from Santa Rosa National Park exhibited a distinctive pattern of setae on the metasoma. In comparison to 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF97FFB00DA6FE3FFD35FE53" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[475,642,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiventris">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB00DA6FE3FFD35FE53" box="[475,642,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">C. longiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the new species has a slightly denser pubescence on the laterals of the metasomal sclerites, and the specimens mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF97FFB00F7EFE1BFC2CFDBF" author="Gauld, I. D." box="[771,923,510,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" pagination="468 - 470" refId="ref6569" refString="Gauld, I. D. (1995) Scolebythidae. In: Hanson, P. E. &amp; Gauld, I. D. (Eds.), Hymenoptera of Costa Rica. Oxford University Press, Oxford, pp. 468 - 470." type="book chapter" year="1995">Gauld (1995)</bibRefCitation>
probably correspond to 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF97FFB008C9FE1BFA86FDBF" authority="Lepeco &amp; Melo, 2022" authorityName="Lepeco &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1204,1329,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pacifica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB008C9FE1BFA86FDBF" box="[1204,1329,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">C. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="90F05517FF97FFB00947FE1BFA22FDBF" bold="true" box="[1338,1429,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="8BC3E86CFF97FFB00947FE1BFA22FDBF" box="[1338,1429,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, although reexamination of the material is needed to confirm its identity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
